is largely insensitive to supporting salt and state of charge. This\nsize is comparable to molecular dimensions of single molecules obtained from\noptimized structures using density function theory calculations. The results\nsuggest that MEEPT is a promising candidate for redox flow batteries in terms\nof its viscous flow properties.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 8 Apr 2020 17:24:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-11-17"}
